The paper discusses a machine learning framework that is designed to be flexible and adaptable to different problems, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-categories within computer science. The focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence makes cs.LG and cs.AI the most likely categories. The mention of data preprocessing and results analysis suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (computer vision) and cs.CL (computational linguistics). Finally, the mention of the need to avoid faulty code suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.SE (software engineering).
